# Fly.io Provider

The Fly.io provider manages infrastructure on the [Fly.io](https://fly.io) platform. It supports the full Fly.io feature set through two layers:

- **REST API** — Apps, machines, volumes, secrets, certificates, network policies, volume snapshots
- **flyctl CLI** — IPs, WireGuard, managed Postgres, Redis, Tigris storage, organizations, tokens, LiteFS, and extensions

## Requirements

- [Terraform](https://developer.hashicorp.com/terraform/downloads) >= 1.11.0
- A [Fly.io account](https://fly.io) with an API token
- [flyctl](https://fly.io/docs/flyctl/install/) (required for Layer 2 resources)

## Authentication

Set your API token via environment variable (recommended):

```bash
export FLY_API_TOKEN="fo1_your_token_here"
```

Or generate one with the Fly.io CLI:

```bash
fly tokens create org
```

